SIMPLE: menstrual
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Menstrual
<hw>Men"stru*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>menstrualis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>menstruel</ets>. See
<er>Menstruous</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Recurring once a month;
monthly; gone through in a month; <as>as, the <ex>menstrual</ex>
revolution of the moon</as>; pertaining to monthly changes; <as>as, the
<ex>menstrual</ex> equation of the sun's place</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the menses; <as>as,
<ex>menstrual</ex> discharges; the <ex>menstrual</ex>
period.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to a menstruum.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Menstruant</ent>⟦br⟧
